er and rely on public APIs, ensuring I stay away from direct reflection. Alternatively, I could create a test class that extends DocumentFactory for proper discovery by JUnit.\\n\\n**Navigating test discovery challenges**\\n\\nI'm considering the test class loading and potential discovery failures due to how methods from DocumentFactory are inherited. It's not ideal. Using MethodHandles seems like direct reflection, which feels less appropriate. Calling a protected method via package doesn't work since they aren't in the same package. I could use a nested subclass, but that might lead to failure if JUnit scans it. Adding a jaxen dependency could help, but it might be too broad. I wonder if a testRuntimeOnly approach for jaxen would work, even though that wouldn’t activate the class.\\n\\n**Revising DocumentFactoryTest**\\n\\nI'm considering re-editing the DocumentFactoryTest to start fresh in a new thread. It seems like a good idea to eliminate the helper class as well. I should follow through with a commit after making these updates. It’s important to keep everything organized and efficient as I make these changes, so I'm planning my next steps carefully. I'll ensure that the code remains clean and easy to understand going forward.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_003dd2ec10db0fff0169f288302164819580c297533f7cc312\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp8og_QD7eafpLzgwRRUeVjhvZE7UUljdHKSdb_LZq39ATjlENPunUcfupBOCWH-Hldt1x1WTtNxFGRZWtQhAlmfj63ABuScKf6t38zsWYf_R4AmtPgD8e9EZy48LfvJtsk7GpEaUQZxrIJ0QDK5ot2iYD4EaKAX-drugYMB8Qo8oHj_a50yIwibqO_DvmF0JvvEUnvkO2XKs60oZbs8Q7y41qo9Srfl41TwrgFBFxpyCtTUFJTYKovd3MD7jTwHIdENzkSprOaRltuV5LS2hYZntHIbmBGkUFjoEt_tjquxdnIiknw0wBdEOiSvjJWl831lr0QFGYcDOLbtWFIMFCukoPo95lkfs8V6iY3UNTeXVqfrHk3-a3iM2rvoH5tJ2nLTmPz4eTNfu4SUO98JUHQ4fb3IDnSj58DoOzCpXO9rOs6ro34JYlfHITNRgramTss6Ym9sc8nD7buGZmkdMC74BYwbI036E3UjbirJJI69L6_4ZbGYqCyih3zbcbkVmzzxnF0WBiBjwBn6dPp7vBGOXh5khpSa7JUSJBFwno5O0G4tyvurInn6n1kdzo_nEwB1