ING_CLASS_NAME));\\n\\n            if (isNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(error)) {\\n                return;\\n            }\\n            assertEquals(MISSING_CLASS_NAME, error.getMessage());\\n        } catch (LinkageError error) {\\n            assertNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(error);\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedNativeImageError(error);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    @Order(1)\\n    void listValuedHeadersCreateOneHeaderForEachValue() throws Throwable {\\n        try {\\n            RequestSpecification requestSpecification = RestAssured.given()\\n                    .headers(Map.of(\\\"X-Trace\\\", List.of(\\\"alpha\\\", \\\"bravo\\\", \\\"charlie\\\")));\\n\\n            QueryableRequestSpecification queryableSpecification = SpecificationQuerier.query(requestSpecification);\\n            Headers headers = queryableSpecification.getHeaders();\\n\\n            assertEquals(List.of(\\\"alpha\\\", \\\"bravo\\\", \\\"charlie\\\"), headers.getValues(\\\"X-Trace\\\"));\\n\\n            Class<?> resolvedClass = resolveWithCompilerGeneratedClassResolver(RESOLVABLE_CLASS_NAME);\\n            Class<?> type = assertInstanceOf(Class.class, resolvedClass);\\n            assertEquals(RESOLVABLE_CLASS_NAME, type.getName());\\n        } catch (LinkageError error) {\\n            assertNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(error);\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedNativeImageError(error);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static Class<?> resolveWithCompilerGeneratedClassResolver(String className) throws Throwable {\\n        return RequestSpecificationImplHeadersClosure6Closure49DirectAccess\\n                .resolveWithCompilerGeneratedClassResolver(className);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void rethrowUnlessUnsupportedNativeImageError(Throwable throwable) throws Throwable {\\n        if (throwable instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        throw throwable;\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void assertNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(LinkageError error) {\\n        assertTrue(isNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(error), () -> \\\"Unexpected initialization failure: \\\" + error);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static boolean isNativeGroovyInitializationFailure(LinkageError error) {\\n        String message = error.getMessage();\\n        return (\\\"Could not initialize class \\\" + CLOSURE_CLASS_NAME).equals(message)\\n                || \\\"Could not initialize class groovy.lang.Closure\\\".equals(message)\\n                || \\\"Could not initialize class groovy.lang.GroovySystem\\\".equals(message)\\n                || \\\"Could not initialize class org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.InvokerHelper\\\".equals(message)\\n                || isGroovySystemInitializerError(error);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static boolean isGroovySystemInitializerError(LinkageError error) {\\n        if (!(error instanceof ExceptionInInitializerError initializerError)) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        Throwable cause = initializerError.getException();\\n        return cause instanceof NullPointerException\\n                && cause.getStackTrace().length > 0\\n                && \\\"groovy.lang.GroovySystem\\\".equals(cause.getStackTrace()[0].getClassName());\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1778450621148}}\n87:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"f8bcde33\",\"parentId\":\"6296f6d7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-10T22:04:04.901Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"**Examining test failures**\\n\\nI'm looking into the test failures. It seems like the native image may not report coverage correctly, but that doesn't necessarily mean there's a failure. The message “newly covered none” suggests there were no test failures, just an issue with coverage. I wonder if the `LinkageError` is causing this. It might be better if we remove catching `LinkageError` from the resolver tests. I think adjusting the order of attempts could resolve the problem.\\n\\n**Adjusting test methods order**\\n\\nI need to check the order of the test methods in XML; it seems like “ReportsMissing” ran before “list” and “Resolves.” That might be causing issues, potentially poisoning the tests. It sounds like changing the order is a good step. I should consider removing separate resolver tests to prevent any ordering issues in parallel runs. To achieve one-to-one coverage, I might also think about removing “resolverReportsMissing.” Directly invoking after the public API could be sufficient in the same method.\\n\\n**Testing list headers**\\n\\nI'm thinking about adding a helper method, specifically for asserting list-valued headers. It looks like I should create one header for each value. Then, I’ll list out the test calls for this helper. I want to resolve the tests by calling this helper before going directly into the main logic. I think some small edits might be required to make everything flow smoothly. This should help ensure that everything's working as intended!\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_035936677ebb4544016a0100bef84481a19f6aea0ed5a3cc6f\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqAQDSoI616ScUGLCF1KDEKCOsCKm5aBxfpVbIwYpSi4MHP9_6Uictrlh2fOayLjeBtpxEt4rbzSPOeD6hU1cY77gnbTtRuY9VGj396zBUATV8xx8nCGKMb5qZlhTV6FnqWVDlQxGJXv66hQc7XE5CQJ8GBe5R6pkD2N-IZSPqwg5Qxh3YjIVJEgKzIBqrSH1j7I3Ww9PUE9zx_nSZWP-oEUeuPHOtq--qRoQy0eH3Akn9ZI6IYcdHhd8ZATLrjYUP65TUzptqWsRL829WCY9xKjEMWzoksd3ZlmfpnlLrw7c-nL7irr3B9XC47C3lMc_8telIYJRMJB2Egfm28bdAr2fwr1J00ZvUbZ9_Vy9diaB4Eq5ixnVtz8rY-58MTXHWBcONbf9Y2s_pr3KbCsWQZI7WHpj1PA7nrKRPpSbaty56DPIbk_5lhSqZu7LjjkeBDZEEQoszM9eZzrioPd0u2G-2PMsO5KdXilyVq5tcyBzr_U3Lan438fJhQUBCDwS0GXd4W_S3X9s4kmRzOe9VaLZko03uCZIyM0cFi48xKvPpCd3pUIRftkV6Z5n0hmziMCZNIITY-4nII6OFwNwMfsQczdbJ2gBfwdpIx3xtrjjm-BI0UdsY70kq6pvo5VT8aBo8zMxu2YeGV1r1P8Um6aSwf2ODJX24rOxxwBBg-GkQpXkND